(2) Master several important distributions, including normal distribution;
(3) Recognize how, when, and why existing inferential tools can be used, including simple linear regression and basic ANOVA;
(4) Understand the context of a business problem, and to apply statistics analysis to solve the problem and to draw conclusions;
(5) Have working knowledge of Excel or other statistic software in terms of basic data analysis tasks.

