courses.course_syllabus:
Topics to Cover

We will cover the following 5 main topics related to the interface between AI and business research in this course:

· Fundamental concepts and hands-on techniques of ML, deep learning (DL), and reinforcement learning (RL) that are useful in business research ;

· AI as data sources (e.g., demand and asset return predictions, feature and label extractions from unstructured text, image, and video data, etc.) to address subsequent relevant business research questions ;

· AI/ML applied to causal models for better identification and/or inference of treatment effects with both observational and experimental data (e.g., double/de-biased machine learning DML, causal trees/forests, matrix completion, doubly-robust estimation, etc.) ;

· AI for optimizing certain business operations in an autonomous and efficient fashion (e.g., online optimization, multi-armed bandit, reinforcement learning, imitation learning, etc.) ;

· AI per se as a subject of study in business research, such as human-algorithm interaction, algorithmic fairness/discrimination, and data privacy, etc.

